.description
  %p
    %strong RubyBench is a long running Ruby benchmark.

    Currently,
    = link_to 'Ruby benchmark scripts',
        'https://github.com/ruby/ruby/tree/trunk/benchmark',
        target: '_blank'
    and
    = link_to 'Discourse benchmark scripts',
        'https://github.com/discourse/discourse/blob/master/script/bench.rb',
        target: '_blank'
    have been implemented and are run for every commit and release. If you've
    noticed a regression, feel free to use RubyBench when opening a new issue.

  %hr

  %h4 Plans

  %p
    RubyBench is currently still in its early stages but has already proven to
    be useful in
    = succeed '.' do
      = link_to 'identifying performance regressions',
          'http://community.rubybench.org/t/ruby-bench-already-helped-catch-a-regression-in-mri',
          target: '_blank'
    We do believe that there are more improvements to be made such as
    providing the percentage difference between commits and releases.
    In the near future, RubyBench will also monitor and track popular Ruby
    libraries such as Rails. In fact, the initial work has
    already
    = succeed '.' do
      = link_to 'started', 'https://github.com/ruby-bench/ruby-bench-docker/tree/master/discourse_benchmarks/rails_head',
          target: '_blank'

  %p
    Help us make RubyBench and Ruby better by contributing to any parts of the
    project:

    %ul
      %li
        Web front-end:
        = link_to 'ruby-bench-web', 'https://github.com/ruby-bench/ruby-bench-web',
            target: '_blank'

      %li
        Benchmark runner:
        = link_to 'ruby-bench-docer', 'https://github.com/ruby-bench/ruby-bench-docker',
          target: '_blank'

  %hr

  %h4 Sponsors

  %p
    We are currently looking for the following sponsors in order to help us
    sustain RubyBench:

    %ol
      %li Hosting sponsor
      %li Bare metal server sponsor

    For parties interested in sponsoring any of the above, please drop us a note
    at our
    = succeed '.' do
      = link_to 'discussion forum', 'http://community.rubybench.org',
          target: '_blank'

  %hr

  %h4 Hardware

  %p
    All benchmarks are run on the same Softlayer bare metal server in order to
    ensure consistent and accurate results. The configuration of the bare metal
    server can be found
    = succeed '.' do
      = link_to 'here', hardware_path
